# Copy to `secret.broker.env` (gitignored; chmod 600), then `./control/broker.sh up`.
# Each line maps an ALIAS to an upstream API and the secret header to inject:
#   <alias> = <upstream-base-url> | <Header-Name: secret value>
#
# The worker Claude calls  $BROKER_URL/<alias>/<path>  with NO credential; the broker adds the
# header on the way out. So Claude can USE these APIs but never READS the tokens.
# These secrets live ONLY in the broker container — workers never receive this file.
#
# Examples (delete / replace with yours):
# github = https://api.github.com | Authorization: Bearer ghp_xxxxxxxx
# stripe = https://api.stripe.com | Authorization: Bearer sk_test_xxxxxxxx
# openai = https://api.openai.com | Authorization: Bearer sk-xxxxxxxx
# internal = https://api.internal.example.com | X-Api-Key: xxxxxxxx
